source: tests/cli_golden.rs
expression: help
---
Install a plugin from a local source directory.

The source must contain a `.aura-plugin/`, `.codex-plugin/`, or `.claude-plugin/` subdirectory with a `manifest.toml`. The install pipeline copies the source tree into the `AURA_HOME/plugins/<id>/<version>/` cache layout and writes a normalised `.aura-plugin.toml` regardless of which alias the source used.

Usage: aura plugins install [OPTIONS] <SOURCE>

Arguments:
  <SOURCE>
          Path to the plugin source directory

Options:
      --mode <MODE>
          Phase 9: top-level `AgentMode` override. Highest rung of the documented resolution priority chain (CLI > TUI slash > SDK field > daemon default > `AgentMode::Agent` fallback). The flag is resolved at session start by the fleet daemon's `resolve_session_mode` helper

          Possible values:
          - agent: Full unrestricted operation subject to user permissions
          - plan:  Read + markdown writes + read-only subprocesses
          - ask:   Read-only
          - debug: Read + sandboxed probes only

      --trust
          Bypass `trust.require_explicit_trust = true` manifests

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
